The DA's organisational review panel recently described Maimane as inconsistent, indecisive and conflict-averse. Courtesy #DStv403 LIVESTREAM: Mmusi Maimane expected to announce his resignation from the DA  JOHANNESBURG - Democratic Alliance leader Mmusi Maimane could be on the verge of stepping down. eNCA has been reliably informed that Maimane will resign. READ: DA shows signs of serious strain On Monday, Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba also resigned from his position. The DA's organisational review panel recently described Maimane as inconsistent, indecisive and conflict-averse. The report was commissioned by Maimane and authored by former DA leader Tony Leon. The panel recommended training for leaders on how to lead a diverse group of people.